 and postcolonial language scholars, the monograph is of interest to researchers and research students in fields such as World Englishes, creole studies, linguistic anthropology, intercultural pragmatics, and global discourse studies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aDiskursanalyse. 4aKognitive Semantik. 4aKulturelle Semantik. 4aPostkoloniale Linguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Historical & Comparative.2bisacsh  acognitive semantics.  acultural semantics.  adiscourse studies.  apostcolonial linguistics.0 cEPUBz97831113380020 cprintz978311133690940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111337432zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111337432zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111337432/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA